cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) for Myanmar language using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing. The sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as it deals with neural network models. The sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the effectiveness of deep neural networks. The sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as NER is a subfield of AI. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as NER is also used in information retrieval systems.
